                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.38/127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 8.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 22nd, 2 p.m. and July 3rd, 5 p.m. Request instructions whether
                    proposed laws submitted by Haitian Government to this Legation for the
                    information of the Government of the United States must be forwarded to
                    Washington and enactment delayed pending expression of opinion thereon by the
                    Department or if, after conference with treaty officials, this Legation is
                    authorized to advise the Haitian Government that there is no objection to the
                    proposed law submitted or, in the event of objections, to enter into discussion
                    relative thereto with the Haitian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
